# Mashed Butternut Squash

![](DAE2B9E6-6748-44B9-8771-92656850D550.jpg)

Preheat oven to 350°F.

- Butternut Squash | 1, 4-5 lbs | 

Cut butternut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out the seeds.

- Butter | ⅓ cup divided | Melted
- Brown Sugar | 2 tbsp | 
- Cinnamon | ¼ tsp | 

Lightly brush the squash with melted butter (reserve the rest for mashing). Sprinkle with spices and brown sugar if using.

Place on a baking sheet cut side up and bake 1 hour to an hour and a half until very tender.

Scoop out the flesh and place in a large bowl.

- Salt | to taste | 
- White Pepper | to taste | 

With a hand masher or an electric mixer on low, mix until smooth. Pour in melted butter to taste. Season with salt & pepper and serve.
